description:
*Summary*

An empty tag set in a read preference appears to reject servers with no tag sets.

*Reproducing*

Start a replica set with a secondary containing no tags:
{code:java}
mlaunch init \
    --replicaset --nodes=2 --name=repl0 --setParameter enableTestCommands=1 \
    --binarypath $HOME/bin/mongodl/archive/8.0.17/mongodb-macos-aarch64-enterprise--8.0.17/bin  \
    --dir .menv
{code}
Run [this repro|https://github.com/kevinAlbs/rust-bootstrap/tree/cd8130352c2c3fdefac73ec8cfdcbaec2438e6e4/investigations/tagset]. It attempts to select a server with with SecondaryPreferred and an empty tag set:
{code:java}
% cargo run --quiet
ERROR: expected to select SECONDARY, but selected PRIMARY
{code}
Testing PyMongo selects the secondary:
{code:java}
% python test-pymongo.py 
OK: selected SECONDARY
{code}
I expect an empty tagset is intended to match a server without tags. Quoting [Server Selection spec|https://github.com/mongodb/specifications/blob/44176c1b633819b5a070e05148a989d0c79d406d/source/server-selection/server-selection.md]:
{quote}The default {{tag_sets}} is a list with an empty tag set: {{{}[{}]{}}}.
{quote}
*Background*
Using a debugger, the secondary appears to get rejected in {{{}matches_tag_set{}}}:
{code:java}
let server_tags = match reply.command_response.tags {
    Some(ref tags) => tags,
    None => return false,
};
{code}
I expect this should be changed to:
{code:java}
let server_tags = match reply.command_response.tags {
    Some(ref tags) => tags,
    None => return tag_set.is_empty(),
};
{code}
